description: The governing party of PM Ludovic Orban could cling to power by allying with smaller parties.
title: Romanian opposition takes narrow lead after election
title_page: Romanian opposition takes narrow lead after election - BBC News
maintext: Turnout was a record low of 33%. Romania is one the poorest countries in the EU and millions of its citizens have moved abroad in recent years in search of better lives - in particular to western EU member states.
